law.catch_line: Attachment, garnishment and levy of execution.
law.text: During the pendency in this or any other state of a liquidation proceeding, whether called by that name or not, no action or proceeding in the nature of an attachment, garnishment or levy of execution shall be commenced or maintained in this state or elsewhere against the delinquent insurer or its assets.
law.history: Created 1970 Ky. Acts ch. 301, subtit. 33, sec. 58, effective June 18, 1970.
